@davehunt r?

This will mean we won't need to update this project every time fxapom is updated

`fxapom` was also to pick up a new version of `PyFxA`, so this project needs to be updated to pick up the new `fxapom`. I think it makes sense to unpin `fxapom` as only this project and marketplace-tests (desktop tests) use it, and we are in full control of all 3 projects.

@davehunt r?

This adds a new test that is part of a Q1 goal.

It also includes a bit of refactoring, as we need to be able to call `switch_to_marketplace_frame` from both the marketplace app object and the payment app object.

@davehunt r?

Change tap() to send_keys() as tap() no longer works

This is discussed in issue #87. We may have to accept this workaround for now, in order to restore coverage, but it deserves more investigation.

